        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>When a customer attempts to register with an invalid phone number (fewer than 10 digits), the system displays the correct validation message “Phone number must be exactly 10 digits”, but the error message is not aligned under the Phone Number input field. This creates a UI inconsistency compared to other field error messages and may confuse users.</p>

<p><b>Steps to Reproduce:</b></p>

<ol>
	<li>Navigate to: <a href="http://localhost:8081/" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">http://localhost:8081/</a></li>
	<li>Click Login button in the top-right corner.</li>
	<li>Click the Register button. (tab)</li>
	<li>Enter valid values in <b>Username</b>, <b>Email</b>, <b>First Name</b>, and <b>Last Name</b> fields.</li>
	<li>In the <b>Phone Number</b> field, enter fewer than 10 digits (1 digit).</li>
	<li>Clicks the Register button.</li>
</ol>




<p><b>Expected Result:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>Validation error message <b>“Phone number must be exactly 10 digits”</b> is displayed.</li>
	<li>The message is <b>left-aligned with the Phone Number input field</b> and appears directly underneath it.</li>
	<li>Spacing, font size, and style match the other validation messages in the form.</li>
</ul>




<p><b>Actual Result:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>Validation error message is displayed: <b>“Phone number must be exactly 10 digits”</b>.</li>
	<li>The message is <b>misaligned</b>, not properly positioned under the Phone Number input.</li>
	<li>UI looks inconsistent compared to other field errors.</li>
</ul>




<p><b>Severity:</b> Minor</p>
